Longa quibus facies ovis erit, &c. “Remember to serve up those eggs which shall have a long shape‚ as being of a better taste, and more nutritious, than the round.” Catius preserves a regular order in delivering his precepts. He begins with the first course of the Roman tables, then proceeds to the fruit, which was called the second table, and ends his remarks with some general reflections upon neatness and elegance.
